messages.messageBody:
Here are some sites that those of you who are into the role
playing/renaissance may fine interesting, if you don't already have them. I
think I got some off this list in the first place. Thought I would post
them since there was a discussion on the subject. I would be interested in
learning more about the Middle Earth roll playing, I am a big Tolkien fan
from way back.

http://www.renaissance-faire.com/ Renaissance faire site

http://www.wsu.edu/~dee/MA/MA.HTM Middle Ages site

http://www.sca.org/ this is the Society for Creative Anachronism site

http://ic.net/~erasmus/RAZ33.HTM something else that looked relevant

http://www.geocities.com/TheTropics/Paradise/8602/index.html living history
renaissance farm, Nanci, check this, it is not that far from you, close to
you than me anyway.
